G5477.strongs_def: Chanaan (i.e. Kenaan), the early name of Palestine

G5478.strongs_def: a Chanaanæan (i.e. Kenaanite), or native of gentile Palestine

G5480.strongs_def: a scratch or etching, i.e. stamp (as a badge of servitude), or scupltured figure (statue)

G5481.strongs_def: a graver (the tool or the person), i.e. (by implication) engraving (("character"), the figure stamped, i.e. an exact copy or (figuratively) representation)

G5482.derivation: from χαράσσω (to sharpen to a point;
G5482.strongs_def: akin to G1125 through the idea of scratching); a stake, i.e. (by implication) a palisade or rampart (military mound for circumvallation in a siege)

G5483.strongs_def: to grant as a favor, i.e. gratuitously, in kindness, pardon or rescue

G5484.derivation: accusative case of G5485 as preposition;
G5484.strongs_def: through favor of, i.e. on account of
G5484.kjv_def: :--be-(for) cause of, for sake of, +…fore, X reproachfully.

G5485.strongs_def: graciousness (as gratifying), of manner or act (abstract or concrete; literal, figurative or spiritual; especially the divine influence upon the heart, and its reflection in the life; including gratitude)
G5485.kjv_def: :--acceptable, benefit, favour, gift, grace(- ious), joy, liberality, pleasure, thank(-s, -worthy).

G5486.strongs_def: a (divine) gratuity, i.e. deliverance (from danger or passion); (specially), a (spiritual) endowment, i.e. (subjectively) religious qualification, or (objectively) miraculous faculty

G5487.strongs_def: to grace, i.e. indue with special honor

G5488.strongs_def: Charrhan (i.e. Charan), a place in Mesopotamia

G5489.strongs_def: a sheet ("chart") of writing-material (as to be scribbled over)

G5490.derivation: from a form of an obsolete primary χάω (to "gape" or "yawn");

G5491.derivation: from a form of the same as G5490;
G5491.strongs_def: a lip (as a pouring place); figuratively, a margin (of water)

G5492.strongs_def: to storm, i.e. (passively) to labor under a gale

G5493.derivation: from the base of G5494 and G4482;

G5494.derivation: from a derivative of χέω (to pour;
G5494.strongs_def: akin to the base of 5490 through the idea of a channel), meaning a storm (as pouring rain); by implication, the rainy season, i.e. winter

G5495.derivation: perhaps from the base of G5494 in the sense of its congener the base of G5490 (through the idea of hollowness for grasping);
G5495.strongs_def: the hand (literally or figuratively (power); especially (by Hebraism) a means or instrument)

G5496.strongs_def: to be a hand-leader, i.e. to guide (a blind person)

G5497.derivation: from G5495 and a reduplicated form of G71;
G5497.strongs_def: a hand-leader, i.e. personal conductor (of a blind person)
kjv_usage: some to lead by the hand

G5498.derivation: neuter of a compound of G5495 and G1125;
G5498.strongs_def: something hand-written ("chirograph"), i.e. a manuscript (specially, a legal document or bond (figuratively))

G5499.derivation: from G5495 and a derivative of G4160;

G5500.derivation: from a comparative of G5495 and τείνω (to stretch);
G5500.strongs_def: to be a hand-reacher or voter (by raising the hand), i.e. (generally) to select or appoint

G5501.strongs_def: from an obsolete equivalent χέρης (of uncertain derivation); more evil or aggravated (physically, mentally or morally)

G5503.derivation: feminine of a presumed derivative apparently from the base of G5490 through the idea of deficiency;
G5503.strongs_def: a widow (as lacking a husband), literally or figuratively

G5504.strongs_def: "yesterday"; by extension, in time past or hitherto

G5506.strongs_def: the commander of a thousand soldiers ("chiliarch"; i.e. colonel

G5508.strongs_def: Chios, an island in the Mediterranean

G5510.derivation: perhaps akin to the base of G5490 (G5465) or G5494 (as descending or empty);

G5512.derivation: from a derivative probably of G5491;
G5512.strongs_def: to throw out the lip, i.e. jeer at

G5514.derivation: feminine of apparently a primary word;

G5516.derivation: the 22nd, 14th and an obsolete letter (G4742 as a cross) of the Greek alphabet (intermediate between the 5th and 6th), used as numbers; denoting respectively 600, 60 and 6;

G5517.strongs_def: dusty or dirty (soil-like), i.e. (by implication) terrene

G5518.strongs_def: a chœnix or certain dry measure

G5520.strongs_def: to be bilious, i.e. (by implication) irritable (enraged, "choleric")

G5521.derivation: feminine of an equivalent perhaps akin to the same as 5514 (from the greenish hue);
G5521.strongs_def: "gall" or bile, i.e. (by analogy) poison or an anodyne (wormwood, poppy, etc.)

G5522.strongs_def: a heap (as poured out), i.e. rubbish; loose dirt

G5524.derivation: from a compound of G5525 and G71;
G5524.strongs_def: to be a dance-leader, i.e. (generally) to furnish

G5526.strongs_def: to fodder, i.e. (generally) to gorge (supply food in abundance)

G5528.strongs_def: a "court" or "garden", i.e. (by implication, of pasture) herbage or vegetation

G5530.derivation: middle voice of a primary verb (perhaps rather from G5495, to handle);
G5530.strongs_def: to furnish what is needed; (give an oracle, "graze" (touch slightly), light upon, etc.), i.e. (by implication) to employ or (by extension) to act towards one in a given manner

G5531.derivation: probably the same as the base of G5530;

G5532.derivation: from the base of G5530 or G5534;
G5532.strongs_def: employment, i.e. an affair; also (by implication) occasion, demand, requirement or destitution

G5533.derivation: from a derivative of G5531 and G3781;

G5534.derivation: third person singular of the same as G5530 or G5531 used impersonally;

G5535.strongs_def: to make (i.e. have) necessity, i.e. be in want of

G5536.strongs_def: something useful or needed, i.e. wealth, price

G5537.strongs_def: to utter an oracle (compare the original sense of G5530), i.e. divinely intimate; by implication, (compare the secular sense of G5532) to constitute a firm for business, i.e. (generally) bear as a title
G5537.kjv_def: :--be called, be admonished (warned) of God, reveal, speak.

G5540.strongs_def: employment, i.e. (specially), sexual intercourse (as an occupation of the body)

G5541.strongs_def: to show oneself useful, i.e. act benevolently

G5542.derivation: from a compound of G5543 and G3004;

G5543.strongs_def: employed, i.e. (by implication) useful (in manner or morals)

G5544.strongs_def: usefulness, i.e. morally, excellence (in character or demeanor)

G5545.strongs_def: an unguent or smearing, i.e. (figuratively) the special endowment ("chrism") of the Holy Spirit

G5546.strongs_def: a Christian, i.e. follower of Christ

G5547.strongs_def: anointed, i.e. the Messiah, an epithet of Jesus

G5548.derivation: probably akin to G5530 through the idea of contact;
G5548.strongs_def: to smear or rub with oil, i.e. (by implication) to consecrate to an office or religious service

G5550.strongs_def: a space of time (in general, and thus properly distinguished from G2540, which designates a fixed or special occasion; and from G165, which denotes a particular period) or interval; by extension, an individual opportunity; by implication, delay
G5550.kjv_def: :--+ years old, season, space, (X often-)time(-s), (a) while.

G5551.derivation: from a presumed compound of G5550 and the base of G5147;
G5551.strongs_def: to be a time-wearer, i.e. to procrastinate (linger)

G5553.strongs_def: a golden article, i.e. gold plating, ornament, or coin

G5554.strongs_def: gold-ringed, i.e. wearing a golden finger-ring or similar jewelry

G5557.derivation: perhaps from the base of G5530 (through the idea of the utility of the metal);
G5557.strongs_def: gold; by extension, a golden article, as an ornament or coin

G5558.strongs_def: to gild, i.e. bespangle with golden ornaments

G5559.derivation: probably akin to the base of G5530 through the idea of handling;
G5559.strongs_def: the body (properly, its surface or skin)

G5561.derivation: feminine of a derivative of the base of G5490 through the idea of empty expanse;
G5561.strongs_def: room, i.e. a space of territory (more or less extensive; often including its inhabitants)

G5562.strongs_def: to be in (give) space, i.e. (intransitively) to pass, enter, or (transitively) to hold, admit (literally or figuratively)
G5562.kjv_def: :--come, contain, go, have place, (can, be room to) receive.

G5563.strongs_def: to place room between, i.e. part; reflexively, to go away

G5564.strongs_def: a spot or plot of ground
G5564.kjv_def: :--field, land, parcel of ground, place, possession.

G5565.strongs_def: at a space, i.e. separately or apart from (often as preposition)

G5567.derivation: probably strengthened from ψάω (to rub or touch the surface;
G5567.strongs_def: compare G5597); to twitch or twang, i.e. to play on a stringed instrument (celebrate the divine worship with music and accompanying odes)

G5568.strongs_def: a set piece of music, i.e. a sacred ode (accompanied with the voice, harp or other instrument; a "psalm"); collectively, the book of the Psalms

G5569.strongs_def: a spurious brother, i.e. pretended associate

G5570.strongs_def: a spurious apostle, i.e. pretended pracher

G5572.strongs_def: a spurious teacher, i.e. propagator of erroneous Christian doctrine

G5573.strongs_def: mendacious, i.e. promulgating erroneous Christian doctrine

G5574.derivation: middle voice of an apparently primary verb;
G5574.strongs_def: to utter an untruth or attempt to deceive by falsehood

G5575.derivation: from G5571 and a kindred form of G3144;
G5575.strongs_def: a spurious witness, i.e. bearer of untrue testimony

G5576.strongs_def: to be an untrue testifier, i.e. offer falsehood in evidence

G5578.strongs_def: a spurious prophet, i.e. pretended foreteller or religious impostor

G5584.derivation: from the base of G5567 (compare G5586);
G5584.strongs_def: to manipulate, i.e. verify by contact; figuratively, to search for

G5585.strongs_def: to use pebbles in enumeration, i.e. (generally) to compute

G5586.strongs_def: a pebble (as worn smooth by handling), i.e. (by implication, of use as a counter or ballot) a verdict (of acquittal) or ticket (of admission); a vote

G5587.derivation: from a derivative of ψίθος (a whisper;
G5587.strongs_def: by implication, a slander; probably akin to G5574); whispering, i.e. secret detraction

G5589.derivation: diminutive from a derivative of the base of G5567 (meaning a crumb);

G5590.strongs_def: breath, i.e. (by implication) spirit, abstractly or concretely (the animal sentient principle only; thus distinguished on the one hand from G4151, which is the rational and immortal soul; and on the other from G2222, which is mere vitality, even of plants: these terms thus exactly correspond respectively to the Hebrew H05315, H07307 and H02416)

G5591.strongs_def: sensitive, i.e. animate (in distinction on the one hand from G4152, which is the higher or renovated nature; and on the other from G5446, which is the lower or bestial nature)

G5594.strongs_def: to breathe (voluntarily but gently, thus differing on the one hand from G4154, which denotes properly a forcible respiration; and on the other from the base of G109, which refers properly to an inanimate breeze), i.e. (by implication, of reduction of temperature by evaporation) to chill (figuratively)

G5595.strongs_def: to supply with bits, i.e. (generally) to nourish

G5596.derivation: diminutive from a derivative of the base of G5597;
G5596.strongs_def: a crumb or morsel (as if rubbed off), i.e. a mouthful

G5597.derivation: prolongation from the same base as G5567;
G5597.strongs_def: to triturate, i.e. (by analogy) to rub out (kernels from husks with the fingers or hand)

G5598.strongs_def: the last letter of the Greek alphabet, i.e. (figuratively) the finality

G5599.strongs_def: as a sign of the vocative case, O; as a note of exclamation, oh

G5600.strongs_def: (may, might, can, could, would, should, must, etc.; also with G1487 and its comparative, as well as with other particles) be
G5600.kjv_def: :--+ appear, are, (may, might, should) be, X have, is, + pass the flower of her age, should stand, were.
kjv_usage: + pass the flower of her age

G5602.derivation: from an adverb form of G3592;
G5602.strongs_def: in this same spot, i.e. here or hither

G5603.strongs_def: a chant or "ode" (the general term for any words sung; while G5215 denotes especially a religious metrical composition, and G5568 still more specially, a Hebrew cantillation)

G5604.strongs_def: a pang or throe, especially of childbirth

G5605.strongs_def: to experience the pains of parturition (literally or figuratively)

G5606.derivation: perhaps from the alternate of G5342;
G5606.strongs_def: the shoulder (as that on which burdens are borne)

G5608.derivation: middle voice from an apparently primary ὦνος (a sum or price);
G5608.strongs_def: to purchase (synonymous with the earlier G4092)

G5610.kjv_def: :--day, hour, instant, season, X short, (even-)tide, (high) time.

G5611.strongs_def: belonging to the right hour or season (timely), i.e. (by implication) flourishing (beauteous (figuratively))

G5612.derivation: middle voice of an apparently primary verb;

G5613.derivation: probably adverb of comparative from G3739;
G5613.strongs_def: which how, i.e. in that manner (very variously used, as follows)
G5613.kjv_def: :--about, after (that), (according) as (it had been, it were), as soon (as), even as (like), for, how (greatly), like (as, unto), since, so (that), that, to wit, unto, when(-soever), while, X with all speed.

G5614.strongs_def: oh save!; hosanna (i.e. hoshia-na), an exclamation of adoration

G5615.derivation: from G5613 and an adverb from G846;
G5615.strongs_def: as thus, i.e. in the same way
G5615.kjv_def: :--even so, likewise, after the same (in like) manner.

G5616.kjv_def: :--about, as (it had been, it were), like (as).

G5619.strongs_def: just as if, i.e. as it were

G5620.strongs_def: so too, i.e. thus therefore (in various relations of consecution, as follow)
G5620.kjv_def: :--(insomuch) as, so that (then), (insomuch) that, therefore, to, wherefore.

G5621.strongs_def: an earlet, i.e. one of the ears, or perhaps the lobe of the ear

G5622.derivation: from a derivative of the base of G5624;

G5623.strongs_def: to be useful, i.e. to benefit
